{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Luk|20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","chapter":20,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":1,"text":"One day as he was teaching the people in the temple and proclaiming the good news, the chief priests and the scribes, with the elders, came","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":2,"text":"and said to him, “Tell us, by what authority are you doing these things? Who is it who gave you this authority?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":3,"text":"He answered them, “I will also ask you a question. Tell me,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":4,"text":"was the baptism of John from heaven or of human origin?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":5,"text":"They discussed it among themselves: “If we say, ‘From heaven,’ he will say, ‘Why didn’t you believe him?’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":6,"text":"But if we say, ‘Of human origin,’ all the people will stone us, because they are convinced that John was a prophet.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":7,"text":"So they answered that they did not know its origin.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":8,"text":"And Jesus said to them, “Neither will I tell you by what authority I do these things.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":9,"text":"Now he began to tell the people this parable: “A man planted a vineyard, leased it to tenant farmers, and went away for a long time.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":10,"text":"At harvest time he sent a servant to the farmers so that they might give him some fruit from the vineyard. But the farmers beat him and sent him away empty-handed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":11,"text":"He sent yet another servant, but they beat that one too, treated him shamefully, and sent him away empty-handed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":12,"text":"And he sent yet a third, but they wounded this one too and threw him out.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":13,"text":"“Then the owner of the vineyard said, ‘What should I do? I will send my beloved son. Perhaps they will respect him.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":14,"text":"“But when the tenant farmers saw him, they discussed it among themselves and said, ‘This is the heir. Let’s kill him, so that the inheritance will be ours.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":15,"text":"So they threw him out of the vineyard and killed him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":16,"text":"He will come and kill those farmers and give the vineyard to others.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":17,"text":"But he looked at them and said, “Then what is the meaning of this Scripture:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":18,"text":"Everyone who falls on that stone will be broken to pieces, but on whomever it falls, it will shatter him.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":19,"text":"Then the scribes and the chief priests looked for a way to get their hands on him that very hour, because they knew he had told this parable against them, but they feared the people.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":20,"text":"They watched closely and sent spies who pretended to be righteous, so that they could catch him in what he said, to hand him over to the governor’s rule and authority.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":21,"text":"They questioned him, “Teacher, we know that you speak and teach correctly, and you don’t show partiality but teach truthfully the way of God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":22,"text":"Is it lawful for us to pay taxes to Caesar or not?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":23,"text":"But detecting their craftiness, he said to them,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":24,"text":"“Show me a denarius. Whose image and inscription does it have?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":25,"text":"“Well then,” he told them, “give to Caesar the things that are Caesar’s, and to God the things that are God’s.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":26,"text":"They were not able to catch him in what he said in public, and being amazed at his answer, they became silent.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":27,"text":"Some of the Sadducees, who say there is no resurrection, came up and questioned him:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":28,"text":"“Teacher, Moses wrote for us that if a man’s brother has a wife, and dies childless, his brother should take the wife and produce offspring for his brother.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":29,"text":"Now there were seven brothers. The first took a wife and died without children.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":30,"text":"Also the second","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":31,"text":"and the third took her. In the same way, all seven died and left no children.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":32,"text":"Finally, the woman died too.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":33,"text":"In the resurrection, therefore, whose wife will the woman be? For all seven had married her.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:34","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":34,"text":"Jesus told them, “The children of this age marry and are given in marriage.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:35","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":35,"text":"But those who are counted worthy to take part in that age and in the resurrection from the dead neither marry nor are given in marriage.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:36","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":36,"text":"For they can no longer die, because they are like angels and are children of God, since they are children of the resurrection.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:37","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":37,"text":"Moses even indicated in the passage about the burning bush that the dead are raised, where he calls the Lord the God of Abraham and the God of Isaac and the God of Jacob.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:38","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":38,"text":"He is not the God of the dead but of the living, because all are living to him.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:39","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":39,"text":"Some of the scribes answered, “Teacher, you have spoken well.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:40","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":40,"text":"And they no longer dared to ask him anything.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:41","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":41,"text":"Then he said to them, “How can they say that the Messiah is the son of David?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:42","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":42,"text":"For David himself says in the Book of Psalms:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:43","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":43,"text":"until I make your enemies your footstool.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:44","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":44,"text":"David calls him ‘Lord.’ How, then, can he be his son?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:45","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":45,"text":"While all the people were listening, he said to his disciples,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:46","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":46,"text":"“Beware of the scribes, who want to go around in long robes and who love greetings in the marketplaces, the best seats in the synagogues, and the places of honor at banquets.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:47","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":20,"verse":47,"text":"They devour widows’ houses and say long prayers just for show. These will receive harsher judgment.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","chapter":20,"paragraphStarts":[1,3,5,8,9,13,14,16,17,18,19,20,23,25,26,27,34,39,41,43,44,45],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"The Authority of Jesus Challenged"},{"beforeVerse":9,"text":"The Parable of the Vineyard Owner"},{"beforeVerse":20,"text":"God and Caesar"},{"beforeVerse":27,"text":"The Sadducees and the Resurrection"},{"beforeVerse":41,"text":"The Question about the Messiah"},{"beforeVerse":45,"text":"Warning against the Scribes"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"One "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 21:23–27","book":"Mat","chapter":21,"verse":23,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 11:27–33","book":"Mrk","chapter":11,"verse":27,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" day as he was teaching "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 19:47","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":47,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" the people in the temple and proclaiming the good news, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 4:18","book":"Luk","chapter":4,"verse":18,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 8:1","book":"Luk","chapter":8,"verse":1,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" the chief priests and the scribes, with the elders, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 9:22","book":"Luk","chapter":9,"verse":22,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 22:66","book":"Luk","chapter":22,"verse":66,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"text","text":" came "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 21:23–27","book":"Mat","chapter":21,"verse":23},{"label":"Mk 11:27–33","book":"Mrk","chapter":11,"verse":27},{"label":"Lk 19:47","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":47},{"label":"Lk 4:18","book":"Luk","chapter":4,"verse":18},{"label":"Lk 8:1","book":"Luk","chapter":8,"verse":1},{"label":"Lk 9:22","book":"Luk","chapter":9,"verse":22},{"label":"Lk 22:66","book":"Luk","chapter":22,"verse":66}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"and said to him, “Tell us, by what authority are you doing these things? Who is it who gave you this authority?”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He answered them, “I will also ask you a question. Tell me, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"was the baptism of John from heaven or of human origin?”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They discussed it among themselves: “If we say, ‘From heaven,’ he will say, ‘Why didn’t you believe him?’ "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But if we say, ‘Of human origin,’ all the people "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 19:48","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":48,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" will stone us, because they are convinced that John was a prophet.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 11:9","book":"Mat","chapter":11,"verse":9,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 7:29–30","book":"Luk","chapter":7,"verse":29,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 19:48","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":48},{"label":"Mt 11:9","book":"Mat","chapter":11,"verse":9},{"label":"Lk 7:29–30","book":"Luk","chapter":7,"verse":29}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So they answered that they did not know its origin."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And Jesus said to them, “Neither will I tell you by what authority I do these things.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 21:33–46","book":"Mat","chapter":21,"verse":33,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 12:1–12","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" he began to tell the people this parable: “A man planted a vineyard,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 5:1–7","book":"Isa","chapter":5,"verse":1,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" leased it to tenant farmers, and went away for a long time. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 21:33–46","book":"Mat","chapter":21,"verse":33},{"label":"Mk 12:1–12","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":1},{"label":"Is 5:1–7","book":"Isa","chapter":5,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"At harvest time he sent a servant to the farmers so that they might give him some fruit from the vineyard. But the farmers beat him and sent him away empty-handed. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He sent yet another servant, but they beat that one too, treated him shamefully, and sent him away empty-handed. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And he sent yet a third, but they wounded this one too and threw him out."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Then the owner of the vineyard said, ‘What should I do? I will send my beloved"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 17:5","book":"Mat","chapter":17,"verse":5,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 3:22","book":"Luk","chapter":3,"verse":22,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" son. Perhaps"},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Other mss add when they see him"},{"kind":"text","text":" they will respect him.’"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 17:5","book":"Mat","chapter":17,"verse":5},{"label":"Lk 3:22","book":"Luk","chapter":3,"verse":22}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Other mss add when they see him"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“But when the tenant farmers saw him, they discussed it among themselves and said, ‘This is the heir. Let’s kill him, so that the inheritance will be ours.’"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 16:16","book":"Luk","chapter":16,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 16:16","book":"Luk","chapter":16,"verse":16}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So they threw him out of the vineyard and killed him."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He will come and kill"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 19:27","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":27,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" those farmers and give the vineyard to others.”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 19:27","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":27}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But he looked at them and said, “Then what is the meaning of this Scripture:"},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit “What then is this that is written"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 4:17","book":"Luk","chapter":4,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 18:31","book":"Luk","chapter":18,"verse":31,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 21:22","book":"Luk","chapter":21,"verse":22,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 21:37","book":"Luk","chapter":21,"verse":37,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 24:44","book":"Luk","chapter":24,"verse":44,"letter":"e"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 4:17","book":"Luk","chapter":4,"verse":17},{"label":"Lk 18:31","book":"Luk","chapter":18,"verse":31},{"label":"Lk 21:22","book":"Luk","chapter":21,"verse":22},{"label":"Lk 21:37","book":"Luk","chapter":21,"verse":37},{"label":"Lk 24:44","book":"Luk","chapter":24,"verse":44}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit “What then is this that is written"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Everyone who falls on that stone will be broken to pieces, but on whomever it falls, it will shatter him.”"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 8:14–15","book":"Isa","chapter":8,"verse":14,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dn 2:34","book":"Dan","chapter":2,"verse":34,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dn 2:44","book":"Dan","chapter":2,"verse":44,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:32–33","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":32,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 2:8","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":8,"letter":"e"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 8:14–15","book":"Isa","chapter":8,"verse":14},{"label":"Dn 2:34","book":"Dan","chapter":2,"verse":34},{"label":"Dn 2:44","book":"Dan","chapter":2,"verse":44},{"label":"Rm 9:32–33","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":32},{"label":"1Pt 2:8","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":8}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then the scribes and the chief priests "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 2:4","book":"Mat","chapter":2,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 20:18","book":"Mat","chapter":20,"verse":18,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 21:15","book":"Mat","chapter":21,"verse":15,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 22:2","book":"Luk","chapter":22,"verse":2,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 23:10","book":"Luk","chapter":23,"verse":10,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" looked for a way to get their hands on him "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 19:47","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":47,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 21:12","book":"Luk","chapter":21,"verse":12,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"text","text":" that very hour, because they knew he had told this parable against them, but they feared the people. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 22:2","book":"Luk","chapter":22,"verse":2,"letter":"h"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 2:4","book":"Mat","chapter":2,"verse":4},{"label":"Mt 20:18","book":"Mat","chapter":20,"verse":18},{"label":"Mt 21:15","book":"Mat","chapter":21,"verse":15},{"label":"Lk 22:2","book":"Luk","chapter":22,"verse":2},{"label":"Lk 23:10","book":"Luk","chapter":23,"verse":10},{"label":"Lk 19:47","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":47},{"label":"Lk 21:12","book":"Luk","chapter":21,"verse":12},{"label":"Lk 22:2","book":"Luk","chapter":22,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 20:15–22","book":"Mat","chapter":20,"verse":15,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 12:13–17","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":13,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" watched closely "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:7","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":7,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 14:1","book":"Luk","chapter":14,"verse":1,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" and sent spies "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 22:15–16","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":15,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" who pretended to be righteous, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or upright"},{"kind":"text","text":" so that they could catch him in what he said, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 11:54","book":"Luk","chapter":11,"verse":54,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" to hand him "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 24:20","book":"Luk","chapter":24,"verse":20,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 3:13","book":"Act","chapter":3,"verse":13,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 8:32","book":"Rom","chapter":8,"verse":32,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"text","text":" over to the governor’s "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 27:2","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":2,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 21:12","book":"Luk","chapter":21,"verse":12,"letter":"k"},{"kind":"text","text":" rule and authority. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 20:15–22","book":"Mat","chapter":20,"verse":15},{"label":"Mk 12:13–17","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":13},{"label":"Lk 6:7","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":7},{"label":"Lk 14:1","book":"Luk","chapter":14,"verse":1},{"label":"Mt 22:15–16","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":15},{"label":"Lk 11:54","book":"Luk","chapter":11,"verse":54},{"label":"Lk 24:20","book":"Luk","chapter":24,"verse":20},{"label":"Ac 3:13","book":"Act","chapter":3,"verse":13},{"label":"Rm 8:32","book":"Rom","chapter":8,"verse":32},{"label":"Mt 27:2","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":2},{"label":"Lk 21:12","book":"Luk","chapter":21,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or upright"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They questioned him, “Teacher, we know that you speak and teach correctly, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 3:2","book":"Jhn","chapter":3,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and you don’t show partiality "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Lit you don’t receive a face"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 1:17","book":"Deu","chapter":1,"verse":17,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 10:17","book":"Deu","chapter":10,"verse":17,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mal 2:9","book":"Mal","chapter":2,"verse":9,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 22:16","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":16,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" but teach truthfully the way of God. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 13:10","book":"Act","chapter":13,"verse":10,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 18:25–26","book":"Act","chapter":18,"verse":25,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jn 3:2","book":"Jhn","chapter":3,"verse":2},{"label":"Dt 1:17","book":"Deu","chapter":1,"verse":17},{"label":"Dt 10:17","book":"Deu","chapter":10,"verse":17},{"label":"Mal 2:9","book":"Mal","chapter":2,"verse":9},{"label":"Mt 22:16","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":16},{"label":"Ac 13:10","book":"Act","chapter":13,"verse":10},{"label":"Ac 18:25–26","book":"Act","chapter":18,"verse":25}],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"Lit you don’t receive a face"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Is it lawful "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:9","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 14:3","book":"Luk","chapter":14,"verse":3,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" for us to pay taxes "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 17:25","book":"Mat","chapter":17,"verse":25,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 23:2","book":"Luk","chapter":23,"verse":2,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 13:6–7","book":"Rom","chapter":13,"verse":6,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" to Caesar "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 2:1","book":"Luk","chapter":2,"verse":1,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 3:1","book":"Luk","chapter":3,"verse":1,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 20:24–25","book":"Luk","chapter":20,"verse":24,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 23:2","book":"Luk","chapter":23,"verse":2,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"text","text":" or not?”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 6:9","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":9},{"label":"Lk 14:3","book":"Luk","chapter":14,"verse":3},{"label":"Mt 17:25","book":"Mat","chapter":17,"verse":25},{"label":"Lk 23:2","book":"Luk","chapter":23,"verse":2},{"label":"Rm 13:6–7","book":"Rom","chapter":13,"verse":6},{"label":"Lk 2:1","book":"Luk","chapter":2,"verse":1},{"label":"Lk 3:1","book":"Luk","chapter":3,"verse":1},{"label":"Lk 20:24–25","book":"Luk","chapter":20,"verse":24},{"label":"Lk 23:2","book":"Luk","chapter":23,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But detecting their craftiness, he said to them, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Other mss add “Why are you testing me?"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Other mss add “Why are you testing me?"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Show me a denarius."},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"A denarius = one day’s wage"},{"kind":"text","text":" Whose image and inscription does it have?”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"A denarius = one day’s wage"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Well then,” he told them, “give to Caesar"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 22:21","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" the things that are Caesar’s, and to God the things that are God’s.”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 22:21","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They were not able to catch him in what he said in public, and being amazed at his answer, they became silent. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 9:36","book":"Luk","chapter":9,"verse":36,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 14:4","book":"Luk","chapter":14,"verse":4,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 9:36","book":"Luk","chapter":9,"verse":36},{"label":"Lk 14:4","book":"Luk","chapter":14,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:27","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Some "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 22:23–33","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":23,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 22:46","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":46,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 12:18–27","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":18,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 12:34","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":34,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" of the Sadducees, who say there is no resurrection, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 23:6","book":"Act","chapter":23,"verse":6,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" came up and questioned him: "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 22:23–33","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":23},{"label":"Mt 22:46","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":46},{"label":"Mk 12:18–27","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":18},{"label":"Mk 12:34","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":34},{"label":"Ac 23:6","book":"Act","chapter":23,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:28","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Teacher, Moses wrote for us that if a man’s brother has a wife, and dies childless, his brother should take the wife and produce offspring for his brother."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 25:5","book":"Deu","chapter":25,"verse":5,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 25:5","book":"Deu","chapter":25,"verse":5,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 25:5","book":"Deu","chapter":25,"verse":5},{"label":"Dt 25:5","book":"Deu","chapter":25,"verse":5}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:29","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now there were seven brothers. The first took a wife and died without children. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:30","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Also the second "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Other mss add took her as wife, and he died without children"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Other mss add took her as wife, and he died without children"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:31","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"and the third took her. In the same way, all seven died and left no children. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:32","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Finally, the woman died too. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:33","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"In the resurrection, therefore, whose wife will the woman be? For all seven had married her.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:34","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Jesus told them, “The children of this age"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 16:8","book":"Luk","chapter":16,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" marry and are given in marriage."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 17:27","book":"Luk","chapter":17,"verse":27,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 16:8","book":"Luk","chapter":16,"verse":8},{"label":"Lk 17:27","book":"Luk","chapter":17,"verse":27}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:35","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But those who are counted worthy"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 5:41","book":"Act","chapter":5,"verse":41,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Th 1:5","book":"2Th","chapter":1,"verse":5,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" to take part in that age"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 10:30","book":"Mrk","chapter":10,"verse":30,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" and in the resurrection from the dead neither marry nor are given in marriage. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ac 5:41","book":"Act","chapter":5,"verse":41},{"label":"2Th 1:5","book":"2Th","chapter":1,"verse":5},{"label":"Mk 10:30","book":"Mrk","chapter":10,"verse":30}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:36","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For they can no longer die,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 15:54–55","book":"1Co","chapter":15,"verse":54,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 21:4","book":"Rev","chapter":21,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" because they are like angels and are children of God,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 82:6","book":"Psa","chapter":82,"verse":6,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 5:45","book":"Mat","chapter":5,"verse":45,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 8:14","book":"Rom","chapter":8,"verse":14,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 8:19","book":"Rom","chapter":8,"verse":19,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 3:26","book":"Gal","chapter":3,"verse":26,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"text","text":" since they are children of the resurrection. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Co 15:54–55","book":"1Co","chapter":15,"verse":54},{"label":"Rv 21:4","book":"Rev","chapter":21,"verse":4},{"label":"Ps 82:6","book":"Psa","chapter":82,"verse":6},{"label":"Mt 5:45","book":"Mat","chapter":5,"verse":45},{"label":"Rm 8:14","book":"Rom","chapter":8,"verse":14},{"label":"Rm 8:19","book":"Rom","chapter":8,"verse":19},{"label":"Gl 3:26","book":"Gal","chapter":3,"verse":26}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:20:37","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Moses even indicated in the passage about the burning bush that the dead are raised, where he calls the Lord the God of Abraham and the God of Isaac and the God of Jacob."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 3:6","book":"Exo","chapter":3,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 3:15","book":"Exo","chapter":3,"verse":15,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 3:6","book":"Exo","chapter":3,"verse":6,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 3:15","book":"Exo","chapter":3,"verse":15,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 4:5","book":"Exo","chapter":4,"verse":5,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 1:2","book":"Mat","chapter":1,"verse":2,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 3:13","book":"Act","chapter":3,"verse":13,"let